 1 CORECALCULATIONMETHOD
 1.1 Step 1: Identify All Functional Groups
 For the target compound, identify and count:
 1.1.1 Water-Compatible Groups (Positive Contributors)
 ‚Ä¢ Hydroxyl groups (‚ÄìOH): +1 point each
 ‚Ä¢ Ether oxygens (‚ÄìO‚Äì): +0.5 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Aminegroups(‚ÄìNH2,‚ÄìNH‚Äì): +0.8 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Carbonyl oxygens (C=O): +0.6 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Carboxyl groups (‚ÄìCOOH): +0.7 points each (when NOT ionized)
 1.1.2 Water-Disruptive Groups (Negative Contributors)
 ‚Ä¢ Sulfonate groups (‚ÄìSO‚àí
 3):‚Äì2.0 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Sulfate groups (‚ÄìOSO‚àí
 3):‚Äì1.8 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Quaternary ammonium (R4N+):‚Äì1.5 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Phosphate groups (‚ÄìOPO2‚àí
 3 ):‚Äì1.2 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Ionized carboxylates (‚ÄìCOO‚àí):‚Äì0.8 points each
 ‚Ä¢ Halogen atoms (F, Cl, Br, I):‚Äì0.3 to‚Äì0.8 points each (iodine worst)
 1.1.3 Scale-Mismatched Groups (Polymer/Macromolecular)
 ‚Ä¢ Longpolymer chains (>10 repeating units):‚Äì0.1 per unit beyond 10
 ‚Ä¢ Highmolecular weight (>1000 Da): Additional‚Äì0.2 to‚Äì0.5 penalty
 1.2 Step 2: Calculate Raw BCS Score
 RawBCSCalculation
 RawBCS =(‚àëWater-CompatiblePoints)‚àí(‚àëWater-Disruptive Points)
 ‚àí(Scale Mismatch Penalty)
 Normalize to 0‚Äì1 Scale:
CODEX BCS ALGORITHM
 4
 BCSnormalized =
 If result < 0, set to 0.
 If result > 1, set to 1.
 RawBCS
 Total number of functional groups counted
 1.3 Step 3: Apply Molecular Context Modifiers
 1.3.1 A. Solubility Penalty
 If water solubility < 1 mg/mL:
 BCSadjusted = BCSnormalized √ó 0.7
 (Poor solubility limits both benefit AND harm)
 1.3.2 B. Molecular Weight Adjustment
 ‚Ä¢ MW<200Da: Noadjustment(optimal for cellular uptake)
 ‚Ä¢ MW200‚Äì500Da: √ó0.95(slight reduction)
 ‚Ä¢ MW500‚Äì1000Da: √ó0.85(moderate reduction)
 ‚Ä¢ MW>1000Da: √ó0.70(significant reduction)
 1.3.3 C. Charge Density Factor
 Charge Density = Number of charged groups
 Molecular weight/100
 If Charge Density > 3 ‚à∂ Multiply BCS by 0.6
 If Charge Density > 5 ‚à∂ Multiply BCS by 0.4
 1.3.4 D. Polymer Dynamics Penalty
 For compounds with repeating units:
CODEX BCS ALGORITHM
 5
 If (Number of repeating units > 10)
 AND(Dynamictimescale > 1ùúás):
 BCSfinal = BCSadjusted √ó 0.5
 1.4 Step 4: Generate Final BCS Score
 FINALBCSSCORECALCULATION
 FINAL BCSSCORE =BCSnormalized √óSolubility Modifier
 √óMWModifier√óChargeModifier
 √óPolymer Modifier
 Round to 3 decimal places.
