 18
 9.3 pH-Dependent Scoring
 Some compounds change ionization with pH:
 9.3.1 Carboxylic acids
 ‚Ä¢ AtpH<pKùëé:‚ÄìCOOH(neutral)‚ÜíScoreas+0.7
 ‚Ä¢ AtpH>pKùëé:‚ÄìCOO‚àí (charged)‚ÜíScoreas‚Äì0.8
 9.3.2 Amines
 ‚Ä¢ AtpH<pKùëé:‚ÄìNH+
 3 (charged) ‚ÜíScoreas‚Äì1.0
 ‚Ä¢ AtpH>pKùëé:‚ÄìNH2 (neutral)‚ÜíScoreas+0.8
 Calculate BCS at physiological pH 7.4 for most applications.
