 10 LITERATURECORRELATIONGUIDE
 10.1 WhattoLookForin Safety Studies
 10.1.1 If BCS predicts POOR (< 0.4), expect to find:
 ‚Ä¢ Inflammatory markers elevated (IL-6, TNF-ùõº, CRP)
 ‚Ä¢ Gutmicrobiome alterations (‚Üì diversity, ‚Üë pro-inflammatory taxa)
 ‚Ä¢ Epithelial barrier dysfunction (‚Üì TEER, ‚Üë permeability)
 ‚Ä¢ Adverse event reports
 ‚Ä¢ Regulatory restrictions or warnings
 ‚Ä¢ Useinresearch to INDUCE disease models
 10.1.2 If BCS predicts GOOD (> 0.7), expect to find:
 ‚Ä¢ GRASstatus or equivalent
 ‚Ä¢ Noadverse effects at recommended doses
 ‚Ä¢ Mayhavetherapeutic benefits
 ‚Ä¢ Longhistory of safe use
 ‚Ä¢ Positive health associations
 10.1.3 If BCS predicts BORDERLINE (0.55‚Äì0.69), expect:
 ‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúGenerally safe‚Äù designation BUT
 ‚Ä¢ Somestudies showing concerns
 ‚Ä¢ Dose-dependent effects
 ‚Ä¢ Conflicting evidence in literature
 ‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúSafe at low doses‚Äù messaging
